<plot>Explores the experience of Japanese-American WWII veterans of the South Bay and Central Coast of California who stepped forward to fight valiantly for their country despite the internment of their families by the U.S. Government. This documentary illuminates their hardships, struggles and bravery and asks the important question: Who can be called an American?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?599910</url></doc>
